{"review": [{"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 0, "sentence": "Authors provide a variant of WGAN, called PC-GAN, to generate 3D point clouds."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 1, "sentence": "The drawback of a vanilla GAN with a DeepSet classifier is analyzed."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 2, "sentence": "The rationality that decoupling the point generator with the object generator is also discussed."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 3, "sentence": "A sandwiching objective function is proposed to achieve a better estimation of Wasserstein distance."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 4, "sentence": "Compared with AAE and the simplified variants of the proposed PC-GAN, the proposed PC-GAN achieves incremental results on point cloud generation."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 5, "sentence": "Comments:"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 6, "sentence": "1. Authors calculate W_U in a primal form via solving an assignment programming problem."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 7, "sentence": "Have authors ever tried Sinkhorn iteration?"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 8, "sentence": "To my knowledge, sinkhorn iteration is a very popular method to solve OT problem effectively."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 9, "sentence": "It would be nice if authors can provide some reasons and comparisons for their choice on the optimizer of W_U."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 10, "sentence": "2."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 11, "sentence": "Authors proved that the sandwiching object W_s is closer to the real Wasserstein distance, but it increases the variance of the loss function."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 12, "sentence": "Specifically, the dynamics of W_U, and W_L, according to lemma1, is (epsilon2-epsilon1)*w(P, G) while the dynamics of W_s is 2*epsilon1 * w(P, G), and 2epsilon1 > epsilon2 - epsilon1 (according to the assumption in lemma 1)."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 13, "sentence": "Does it mean that the W_s is not as stable as W_L or W_U during training?"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 14, "sentence": "Additionally, authors combined W_U with W_L with a mixture 20:1, i.e., the s in Eqs(6, 13, 14) is smaller than 0.05."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 15, "sentence": "In such a situation, both the value and the dynamics of W_s will be very close to that of W_U. Does it mean that W_L is not so important as W_U?"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 16, "sentence": "Authors should analyze the stability of their method in details."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 17, "sentence": "Essentially, the proposed method is a variant of WGAN, which estimates Wasserstein distance with lower bias but may suffer from worse stability."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 18, "sentence": "In the experiments, both the setting and the experimental results show that the proposed W_s will be very close to W_U. As a result, the improvement caused by the proposed method is incremental compared with its variants."}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 19, "sentence": "Typos:"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 20, "sentence": "- The end of the 2nd line of lemma 1: P, G should be \\mathbb{P}, \\mathbb{G}"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 21, "sentence": "- The 3rd line of lemma 1: epsilon1 -> epsilon_1"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 22, "sentence": "- Page 14, Eq(14), \\lambda should be s"}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 23, "sentence": "- Page 14, Eqs(13, 14), w(\\mathbb{P}, \\mathbb{G}) should appear on the right."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": 