labels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 14, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Quote", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 15, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Clarification", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 16, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 17, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 18, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Originality", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 19, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 20, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Typo", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 21, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Typo", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 22, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Typo", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "H1eZXehVnX", "sid": 23, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Typo", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 0, "sentence": "We thank reviewer for his insightful comments."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 1, "sentence": "1."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 2, "sentence": "We agree with the reviewer that sinkhorn iteration is a way to obtain an upper bound on Wasserstein distance."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 3, "sentence": "However, based on the original paper, they solve the Sinkhorn divergen with T iterations, later when they solve the generator based on the estimated distance, the gradient has to backpropagate through those T iterations, which is expensive and infeasible."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 4, "sentence": "We also note that there is new work, IPOT (Xie et al., 2018), which can get rid of backpropagating through the T iterations as what we adopted (Bertsekas, 1985) in the paper."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 5, "sentence": "Combining PC-GAN with IPOP or other future works could be an interesting future work."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 6, "sentence": "2.  The variance of the sandwiched estimator can be higher, but we are more concerned about bias in this work, which can be treated as a bias-variance trade-off."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 7, "sentence": "3. The 20:1 mixture used in practice do not directly correspond to s in theory, because the distances we compute are not scaled."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 8, "sentence": "For example, if the f_\\phi, the discriminator of GAN, is k-Lipschitz, the lower bound estimate should be divided by k."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 9, "sentence": "However, k is unknown in practice."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 10, "sentence": "Therefore, we just numerically did a coarse grid search and find the best mixture ratio."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 11, "sentence": "Also, we try different ratios as we replied to R2 above."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 12, "sentence": "Ratio                   D2F (Distance to Face)"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 13, "sentence": "Coverage"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 14, "sentence": "1:0"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 15, "sentence": "6.03E+00                        3.36E-01"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 16, "sentence": "40:1"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 17, "sentence": "6.06E+00                       3.41E-01"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 18, "sentence": "20:1"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 19, "sentence": "5.77E+00                       3.47E-01"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 20, "sentence": "10:1"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 21, "sentence": "6.85E+00                       3.56E-01"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 22, "sentence": "0 :1"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 23, "sentence": "9.19E+00                       3.67E-01"}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 24, "sentence": "4. We do not consider W_s to be very close from W_U. As can be seen from Figure 6, for the aeroplane examples, W_U fails to capture aeroplane tires while W_s can."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 25, "sentence": "Similarly for Chair example, W_s recovers better legs than W_U. Quantitatively, we highlight that W_s outperforms W_U consistently as shown in Table 1."}, {"text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 26, "sentence": "Thus, we consider both W_U and W_L is needed to generate good quality point clouds."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "social", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7, 8, 9], "responsetype": "concede-criticism", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7, 8, 9], "responsetype": "reject-request_scope_No", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 3}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7, 8, 9], "responsetype": "mitigate-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "r1eAuTlLCX", "sid": 4}, {"labels": {"alignments": [6, 7, 